@prefix : <https://www.somusicvocabulary.org/music#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

# NEGATIVE: :MusicalPersonShape — the coverage hole this release opened.
#
# v3.0.0 moved conductors and producers OUT of :Musician (which :MusicianShape policed) and
# into :MusicalPerson — a class that, as introduced, NO shape targeted. The four individuals
# the release created (Karajan, Bernstein, Rubin, Martin) landed in an unvalidated hole: they
# could carry a non-instrument :hasInstrument, a bogus :hasGenre and an untyped :bornOn and
# still pass clean. Identical garbage on a :Musician failed immediately.
#
# A redesign that relocates a population must relocate its constraints too.

:NEG_UnvalidatedPerson a :MusicalPerson ;
    rdfs:label "Negative fixture — a person with garbage in every slot"@en ;
    :hasInstrument :NEG_NotAnInstrument ;
    :bornOn "sometime in the 1930s" ;   # untyped string where an xsd:gYear belongs
    .

:NEG_NotAnInstrument a :RecordLabel ;
    rdfs:label "Negative fixture — emphatically not an instrument"@en ;
    .
